Fix TrustRegionNewton losing the problem dimension in CppNumericalSolvers v2.0.0.

InitializeSolver() sets `dim_` from the initial point and then calls
ResetInternal(), which sets `dim_ = 0`. The CG-Steihaug subproblem solver then
reads `dim_` (== 0) and allocates a size-0 step vector; the first
`p + alpha * direction` update mixes a size-0 and a size-n vector and aborts
inside Eigen on every dynamically-sized problem. Reorder the two statements so
`dim_` is assigned last.

Upstream: https://github.com/PatWie/CppNumericalSolvers (v2.0.0)

--- a/include/cppoptlib/solver/trust_region_newton.h
+++ b/include/cppoptlib/solver/trust_region_newton.h
@@ -184,5 +184,8 @@
   void InitializeSolver(const FunctionType& /*function*/,
                         const StateType& initial_state) override {
-    dim_ = initial_state.x.rows();
     ResetInternal();
+    // Patched (magmaan): upstream v2.0.0 set dim_ then called ResetInternal(),
+    // which zeroes dim_ -- the CG subproblem then built a size-0 step vector
+    // and aborted. Assigning dim_ after ResetInternal() restores the sizing.
+    dim_ = initial_state.x.rows();
   }
